{{Infobox language |name=Barkul |nativename=Bo-Rukul |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Plateau State]] |speakers=2,000 |date=1999 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Plateau languages|Plateau]] |fam5=[[East Plateau languages|East]] ? |dia1=Bo |dia2=Rukul |iso3=mae |glotto=boru1244 |glottorefname=Bo-Rukul }}{{Infobox ethnonym|amaBɔ|baBɔ|Kap amaBɔ|5=Bo}}{{Infobox ethnonym|amaRukul|baRukul|Kap maRukul|5=Rukul}}
'''Barkul''' (Bo-Rukul) is a [[Plateau language]] of [[Nigeria]]. The two dialects, Bo and Rukul, are notably distinct. The classification of Barkul is unclear, but it appears to be closest to [[Fyam language|Fyam]] and [[Horom language|Horom]].
==References== {{Reflist}}
