{{Infobox language |name=Biseni |nativename= |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Rivers State]] |ethnicity=[[Buseni tribe|Buseni]] |speakers=4,800 |date=1977 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Ijoid languages|Ijoid]] |fam3=[[Ijaw languages|Ijaw]] |fam4=West |fam5=Inland |iso3=ije |glotto=bise1238 |glottorefname=Biseni }}
'''Biseni''' (Buseni) is one of three small [[Ijaw languages|Inland Ijaw languages]] of [[Nigeria]]. According to ''Ethnologue'', it is not fully [[Mutual intelligibility|intelligible]] with other varieties of Inland Ijaw.
