{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Isakhel |image =Tribal and religious leaders in southern Afghanistan.jpg |caption = |poptime = |popplace = {{flagcountry|Pakistan}} |langs = [[Pashto language|Pashto]] • [[Saraiki dialect|Saraiki]] • [[Urdu]] • [[English language|English]] |rels = [[File:Allah-green.svg|18px]] [[Sunni Islam]] |related = [[Pashtun people|Pashtuns]] • [[Niazi]] | }} '''Isakhel''' is a sub-tribe of the Pashtun tribe, [[Niazi]]. The earliest recorded mention of the isa khel tribe is in [[Baburnama]], 1504-1505.<ref name="Baburnama">{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/stream/baburnamainengli01babuuoft#page/232/mode/2up/search/Isa-khail |title="Bāburnāma" Memoirs of Ẓahīr-ud-Dīn Muhammad Bābur (1483–1530), founder of the Mughal Empire |p=233–234}}</ref> Most of the tribe still resides in their ancestral town of [[Isakhel]], named after their ancestor [[Isa Khan Niazi]], but a lot have shifted to bigger cities or different towns in pursuit of a better education and better opportunities.
==Clans== * '''Zakku Kheyl'''Many clan tribes of southern area of isa khel city belong to this tribe, most influencial due to their English Empire connections has been Khan Zaman Khels, they captured more area than their ancestral part in the lands of isa khel">{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.1736/2015.1736.A-Year-On-The-Punjab-Frontier-Vol-i-In-1848-49#page/n427/mode/2up |title=A Year On The Punjab Frontier Vol-1 In 1848-49 by Edwardes Herbert B. |p=282 & 388}}</ref> * '''Mammu Khel''' Earlier/Former Chiefs of Isa Khel Tribe after Isa Khan till 1748 before Zakku Khels who became chief with the help of Ahmad Shah Abdali in a coup in 1748. This tribe mainly live in southern suburbs and villages of Isa Khel comprising 60% population of Isa Khel tribe. The names of their villages are Khaglanwala, Behu (s) (i.e. Saido Khel, Beram Khel and Hakeem Khel),Sarwar Khel, Wandha Ghalay Khel, Attock Paniala, Khira in Lukki Marwat District. The names of some notable sub-clans are Khizar Khel, Ahmad Khel, Ghazi Khel, Azeem Khel,Sherkhani,Fateh Khani,Wadday,Nasir Khel,Daulat Khel (Saido Khel), Pahar Khel,Ghali Khel, Beram Khel,Hakeem Khel, Shamsi Khel (Umar Khel, Haji Khel, Jhangi Khel (Nourang Khel), Machi Khel, Sarwar Khel) <ref name="Notes on Afghanistan and Baluchistan by Major Henry">{{cite web |url=https://i.imgur.com/b7ujax3.jpg |title=Notes on Afghanistan and Baluchistan by Major Henry |p=343–371}}</ref><ref name="A year in the punjab">{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.1736/2015.1736.A-Year-On-The-Punjab-Frontier-Vol-i-In-1848-49#page/n427/mode/2up |title=A Year On The Punjab Frontier Vol-1 In 1848-49 by Edwardes Herbert B. |p=282 & 388}}</ref>
* '''Appoo Khel''' People of this clane live in Isa Khel city with unchanged name of Appo Khel<ref name = "A year in the punjab"/> * '''Badunzye'''<ref name = "A year in the punjab"/> ( The clane of Maulana Abdussattar Khan Niazi i.e.Bahadur Khel,others are Multani Khel, Oria Khel, Umar Khel) * '''Nakhmad''' ( Perali khel (Pahar Khel, Yaqoob Khel (Said Khel, Ghazi Khel) )
