| foreign  = [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[French language|French]] and [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]
| sign      = [[French Sign Language]], [[Catalan Sign Language]]
}}

The following languages are spoken in the Principality of [[Andorra]].

== Catalan ==
{{main|Catalan language}}
[[File:Sign in Catalan in Andorra.jpg|thumb|Most signage in Andorra is monolingual in Catalan]]
Catalan is the only official language of Andorra.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andorramania.com/constit_gb.htm |title=Constitution of Andorra (Article 2.1)}}</ref> It is also the historical and traditional language of the country used by government, television, radio, and other national media and is the main language of all the people living in the territory of Andorran nationality, who constitute 33% of the total population.{{citation needed|date=January 2013}}

It is also the main language of about 25% of Spanish immigrants (who constitute 43% of Andorra's population), usually those who immigrated since 1985 from nearby [[Catalonia]] or [[Valencian Community|Valencia]].{{citation needed|date=January 2013}}

Recently the [[Government of Andorra]] is enforcing the learning and use of the language within the immigrant labor force as a means to fully apply the constitution and overcome the issue of people living in a country without knowing its only native language. Despite vast incoming tourism from Spanish-speakers from Spain, both public and private signage in Andorra is mostly monolingual in Catalan.<ref name=girona>{{cite web|url=http://www.romaniaminor.net/ianua/ianua04/ianua04_08.pdf|format=PDF|title=El català a Andorra: tota una lluita|first=Guillem|last=Molla|publisher=Universitat de Girona|language=it|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022071534/http://www.romaniaminor.net/ianua/ianua04/ianua04_08.pdf|archivedate=2013-10-22|df=}}</ref>

Andorra is the only country in which Catalan is the sole official language<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gencat.cat/llengua/noves/noves/hm03primavera/catalana/a_farras.pdf | title=The  sociolinguistic situation in Andorra: results of differents studies | accessdate=1 May 2016 | author=Farràs, Jaume}}</ref> and the only country in which Catalan has official status in all of its territory.

== Spanish and Galician ==
{{main|Spanish language|Galician language}}
Spanish is the most important languange in Andorra after Catalan. It is the main language of about 70% of [[Spanish people|Spanish]] national immigrants (the remaining 5% speak [[Galician language|Galician]]). Most came to the country between 1955 and 1985.

The low degree of development of Andorra, the limited education in the immigrants' homelands, and the fear of an invasion by Spain during the [[Franco regime]] made it more difficult for the immigrants to integrate fully until 1993, when the constitution of the country was approved.{{citation needed|date=January 2013}} Since then, Spanish has become the second most used language of the population living in the country,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catala.ad/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=42&Itemid=115|title= Tractaments protocul-laris|work= Estudi sociolingüístic del 2004|publisher=Principality of Andorra|language=ca}}</ref> and moreover is the dominant language of communication amongst people of different linguistic backgrounds—"the language of the street", thus triggering recent government efforts to promote more general and universal use of Catalan.<ref name=girona/>

Since Andorra also shares both Catalan and French education systems, children can learn Spanish if parents choose the Catalan option.

== Portuguese ==
{{main|Portuguese language}}
The traditional economic situation in Northern Portugal ([[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]) prompted a large migration flux to the country between 1960 and 1980, increasing the Portuguese population to 11% of the total, which added to a small community of [[Brazilian people|Brazilians]] which migrated to Andorra in the 1990s has led to a present-day [[portuguese language|lusophone]] population of about 13% of the country's total.{{citation needed|date=June 2012}}

== French ==
{{main|French language}}
The nearby border with [[France]], the reduced tax-free cost of living, and job opportunities in the thriving tourist industry have resulted in 7% of the country's total population being French nationals, mainly immigrants from [[Francophone Africa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadistica.ad|title= Departament d'Estadistica|publisher=principality of Andorra|language=ca}}</ref> It is the main language of communication next to Catalan in [[Pas de la Casa]] on the French border.<ref name=girona/>

As with Spanish, children can be taught at school in the French language, if parents so choose.

